<dl id="n57076b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n57" href="#n57076b">N57 (VI.B.47)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n57all.htm#n57076b"> 76(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> adorn / purana / <font color="green">[traditions]</font></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Es gilt, die Alten &Uuml;berlieferungen (Purana) indischen Glaubens und Lebens mit ihren Mythensch&auml;tzen aufzubl&auml;ttern, um ihre Traumbilder g&ouml;ttlicher Gewalten und Weltschicksale in unsere Sprache umzuschreiben. <br><font color="green">[We only have to leaf through the <mark>Old Traditions (Purana)</mark> of Indian belief and life with their treasures of myths, to translate their dream images of the divine powers and world-destiny into our own language.]</font> <small> Heinrich Zimmer, <a name="HZMI2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#HZMI2"><cite title="source">Maya der indische Mythos</cite></a> (1936) 36</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
